NUMBER 3850
NAME Swamp, clearing
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
SWAMP
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rotting vines clinging to blackened branches, shattered stumps, the only
remnants of once vibrant trees, and the fetid stench of still swamp water
combine to give this deep part of the swamp an aura of decay. Rising above
the tangled treetops to the east are two towers, one of white and one of
deep, inky blackness...
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 152
EXIT E 3851
ITEM 0 229
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Once a vibrant testament to nature's power the large tree now clings to
the last remnants of its strength, fighting a tenacious, but losing, battle
against the elements of decay that surround it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The fading roar of an angry skrag resounds in the distance.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The sharp odor of still swamp water is nearly overpowering here.
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 0
  IFVAR SKILL17 > 1
    ECHO PLAYER A startling sense of displacement rushes from the tree into your mind, as if the tree were attempting to communicate something to you. Unfortunately the feeling fades almost as quickly as it came.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
CEVENT 62 100 3850
   RANDOM dummy3 1 10 0
     IFVAR dummy3 = 1
       AFFECT 3852
       ECHO ALL A ghostly scene is played out before you...
       ECHO ALL A black-robed figure gestures and a beautiful woman, clad in white, is bound in magical bands of force. Tears stream down her face as the black-robed figure advances upon an older man, tied to a chair. The older man gazes up at the black-robed figure with a pleading look in his eyes, but it is for naught as the robed figure crushes the skull of the older man...the young woman screams in anguish as the scene fades...
     ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3851
NAME Swamp, fork
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
SWAMP
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ground becomes firmer as the land rises out of the waters of the swamp.
Two narrow trails have been forged through the thick expanses of swamp
vegetation to the northeast and east. Black vines cover a tiny path to the
south, their tips brushing lazily against the ground. To the northeast lies
the magnificent edifice of the white tower, while the brooding presence of
the black tower lies to the east.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3853
EXIT E 3854
EXIT W 3850
ITEM 0 80 VAL2=3852
ITEM 9 693
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The droning of insects fills your ears with a monotonous rhythm.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3852
NAME Swamp, ruined cottage
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Nature, in the form of vines and moss, have nearly reclaimed this small
patch of ground but small bits of the structure that once stood here still
remain. A crumbling fireplace and chimney still thrust out of the ground,
forming the eastern wall of what you now take to be a simple cottage. The
few rotting planks still remaining on the ground indicate where the other
walls once stood. Scattered around the area, mostly hidden by the thick
growth are various rusted, and useless, metal tools and a few shattered
pieces of pottery. A simple headstone juts out of the ground at a skewed
angle a few feet behind the fireplace. A tiny path leads back towards the
fork.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 80 VAL2=3851
ITEM 1 195 ADJ1=533
EXTEND 1 covered with moss
ITEM 2 1907
ITEM 3 390
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Moss covers the loose bricks that make up the fireplace and chimney. A
few ashes still cover the interior of the fireplace, remnants of the
last fire built by the cottages inhabitants.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Dead vines and green moss cover most of the headstone, but you can still
make out the writing upon its face...
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
                  "Miyana"
          "Beloved mother and wife"
                 "543-594"
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
The skeleton has been picked clean of flesh, even though a few insects still
crawl over it, searching for a meal. Though long grass and moss obscures
most of the bones, you are able to discern that the skull has been crushed
in by a blunt instrument and the ribcage has been torn open, perhaps by
the jaws of some powerful animal...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
  IFVAR SKILL30 => 10
  RANDOM dummy1 1 10 0
    IFVAR dummy1 = 10
      ECHO PLAYER Your spine tingles as you gaze across the area, you get a sense of something trapped, something screaming out in anguish from its prison...
      ECHO OTHERS %N shudders and looks around carefully.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER A shrill moaning is carried on the wind as it whistles through the trees. The eerie resonance of sound is strangely disquieting...
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER You push aside some vines and discover a skeleton inside the ruined cottage.
  ECHO OTHERS %N points out something %s found inside the ruined cottage.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 3
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 980
    REMOVEITEM -1
    ECHO ALL The wind picks up, blowing in fierce gusts, as the entire area becomes darker. A terrible moan cuts through the wind and then you see a shadowy specter rise from the skeleton. The specter, virtually without shape or form, turns to gaze balefully at you. It cries horribly, a cry of pain and anguish, and then begins to speak in a chilling sepulchral tone....
    ECHO ALL "My own flesh and blood did this to me! My own son!!! To sate his diabolical quest for dark knowledge he killed his own father." The spectre moans, sadly this time, before continuing, "In front of his own sister no less. Her white magic contained by his fell power, he made her watch as he struck me with his staff. He made her watch as he tore me open, taking parts of me to use in his experiments. Trapped now forever, bound to this place by my own body..." The specter looks sorrowfully about, wails once more and then sinks back into the ground.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3853
NAME Swamp, white tower
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The dark trees shrink back from the still magnificent beauty of gleaming
white building which rises towards the sky. A small garden of wilted flowers
surrounds the base of the tower, their once colorful beauty stilled by the
passage of time. In front of the white marble arch that leads inside is a
cracked and weathered statue of a handsome warrior. Your attention is brought
to the top of the tower where a tattered pennant snaps and unfurls in the
gusting wind. The towering, vine-covered swamp trees obscure most of the back
of the tower, but you think that you can make out some sort of catwalk
leading into the treetops from the rear of the tower.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 3851
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=187 VAL2=2601
ITEM 1 346
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Though weathered by time the finely sculpted statue still retains a degree
of dignity and bearing. The handsome male warrior that it portrays is
distinguished by the beautiful sword that he wields. One side of the blade
seems to be composed of flames, while the other side is composed of
crystalline ice.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER Straining your hearing to your outermost limits you faintly hear a single, never-ending note of music that seems to drift from the very walls of the tower.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The lingering scent of crushed rose petals is a pleasant counterpoint to the swamp gas present elsewhere.
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
  IFVAR ALIGN < -10
    ECHO PLAYER A sweet, lyrical voice, tinted with an edge of anger, fills your mind, "Beware scion of darkness! Disturb not my home!"
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The sword sparks a faint chord in your mind. You vaguely recall reading of a warrior wielding a sword that fits that description. The warrior lived some 500 hundred years ago.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER The sword sparks a faint chord in your mind. You vaguely recall reading of a warrior wielding a sword that fits that description. The warrior lived some 500 hundred years ago.
    ECHO PLAYER Concentrating a bit harder you remember reading that the warrior's name was Nerral Ingvor and the blade's name, "Icefire".
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 3
    ECHO PLAYER The sword sparks a faint chord in your mind. You vaguely recall reading of a warrior wielding a sword that fits that description. The warrior lived some 500 hundred years ago.
    ECHO PLAYER Concentrating a bit harder you remember reading that the warrior's name was Nerral Ingvor and the blade's name, "Icefire".
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER The sword sparks a faint chord in your mind. You vaguely recall reading of a warrior wielding a sword that fits that description. The warrior lived some 500 hundred years ago.
    ECHO PLAYER Concentrating a bit harder you remember reading that the warrior's name was Nerral Ingvor and the blade's name, "Icefire".
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 => 5
    ECHO PLAYER The sword sparks a faint chord in your mind. You vaguely recall reading of a warrior wielding a sword that fits that description. The warrior lived some 500 hundred years ago.
    ECHO PLAYER Concentrating a bit harder you remember reading that the warrior's name was Nerral Ingvor and the blade's name, "Icefire".
    ECHO PLAYER The legend goes that Nerral forged his sword in the bowels of the earth with the aid of a Deeplander smith and the knowledge of a Dragon. Nerral then fought his way back to the woman he loved, who was supposed to live within a white tower...
  ENDIF
ENDIF
