NUMBER 3854
NAME Swamp, black tower
OUTDOOR_OTHER
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tall weeds and dying moss cover the base and sides of the tall black tower
that sits in the gloom of the drooping trees surrounding it. The tower's
shape is that of a brooding obelisk, without any windows and only a single
black arch allowing entrance. The arch itself is luridly carved with the
grinning visages of demons, the eyes of which seem to follow your every
move. Extending from the rear of the tower, at the top, seems to be a
stone catwalk. The catwalk disappears into the thick treetops before you
can gauge where it ends.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3851
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=25 VAL2=3855
ITEM 9 693
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The oppressive edifice before you seems to mute all sound.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The foul miasma of the swamp is thick here, almost as if everything foul about the swamp emanated from this single place.
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
  IFVAR ALIGN < -20
    ECHO PLAYER A cold voice, devoid of all emotion but cruelty and hate, fills your mind, "Greetings, may you find my abode to your liking kin of darkness."
  ENDIF
    IFVAR ORG = 1
      ECHO PLAYER A cold, cruel voice fills your mind, "May the path you walk upon always be filled with the expanding knowledge of darkness fellow Shadowmancer."
    ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3855
NAME Black Tower, inside
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A faint layer of dust covers the entirety of the first floor. The dust
obscures the eerily beautiful black stone from which the tower is made of.
Deep shadows lurk in the corners, extending out to drape the walls like
immaterial curtains. A circular staircase ascends to the upper floors of
the tower, while an arch offers exit to the relative safety of the swamp.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 3856
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=25 VAL2=3854
ITEM 1 420
ITEM 9 693
EXTEND 1 draped in dark shadows
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
You gaze at the wall for a long time trying to discern any details. The
shadows flow across the wall, moving, it seems, to keep you from being
able to see whatever they hide. You catch glimpses of bright stars and
evil, leering faces. Just as you are turning away you catch a glimpse of
a streaking comet and a strange face behind it...
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 118
