NUMBER 3857
NAME Black Tower, wall of bones
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You slip and stumble as you walk across the floor of this macabre chamber.
The entire chamber is made up of bones of all shapes and sizes. The bones
are stuck to the walls, ceiling and, you think, the floor. There seems to
be no pattern to the placement of the bones, just a seemingly jumbled mess.
The strangely magical mist is thicker here, roiling around in large clouds
that entirely cover the floor before some of it seeps out of the chamber
and moves to the south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3856
ITEM 0 420
ITEM 9 693
EXTEND 0 of bones
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
A close inspection of the ghoulish wall tells you that it seems to be the
source of the mist, for you can see it seeping past the tiny cracks in the
jumbled together bones.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 118
IFVERB THUMP 0
  ECHO PLAYER The wall vibrates slightly and some of the bones move a small distance, as if they were trying to join with other bones.
  ECHO OTHERS The wall vibrates slightly as %N thumps on it. The vibrations cause some of the bones to move towards each other, as if they were trying to join together...
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The grating of bone against bone sets your teeth on edge.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3858
NAME Black Tower, webbed hall
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A large number of of white webs, glistening with a faint bluish tint, stretch
across the eastern end of this hallway like a giant wall. You catch faint
glimpses of a chamber beyond the web, but details are impossible to make out.
A corpse, bound in silken strands, hangs from the top of the wall of webs.
Judging by the size of the webs, the spider that made them must be extremely
large, and probably very deadly...
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3856
ITEM 0 420
EXTEND 0 of webs
ITEM 1 232
EXTEND 1 cocconed inside the web
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The corpse has mummified with time, leaving only a dessicated shell. You can
determine that the corpse is of a human male, perhaps a servant of some kind
judging by its clothing. A look of panic-stricken horror is etched across the
corpse's face.
*DESCRIPTION_END
