IFPREVERB TURN 5
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR zagor = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You flip to another page.
    ECHO OTHERS %N flips to another page.
    ADD zagor1 1
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 5
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR zagor = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The book is impressively bound in black leather and seems to have escaped most of the ravages of time.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The book is open to a page.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 5
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR zagor1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER "The Journal of Zagor the Black"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor1 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER "I have been accepted with open arms into an organization whose goals are the same as mine! Their quest for magical knowledge and power is neverending, and they concern themselves not with pondering upon ethics and morals, like the uptight members of the Silver Arcana. I see great rewards to be gained as I travel down the paths of darkness in my search for the power I wish to wield."
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor1 = 3
    ECHO PLAYER "Many are the things I have learned with my fellow brethren! One in particular, I will not mentions his(?) name, but he(?) is particularly adept at dealing with the forces of darkness. We have discovered a means to animate the bones of the dead into guardian creatures. Oh, if only my sister were not so uptight! The power I could show her, but she only plays at magic and will never fully realize the might she could wield. She is even now turning my father against me, and imploring me to turn from my chosen path."
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor1 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER "There is no turning back now. Earlier today I slew my father, but as N. pointed out, a price must sometimes be paid. My sister tried to meddle, but my magics kept her contained until the deed was done. I took what I needed from my father, and will now begin the creation of my armies."
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor1 = 5
    ECHO PLAYER "Moons rise above my head, Are they Living embodiments of my power? Keen insight will be mine for Twenty days And a year"
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR zagor1 => 6
    ECHO PLAYER This is the last page.
    ECHO PLAYER "My sister seeks to stop me. She calls from the catwalk, I go now to put and end to her meddling. If all fails, I will return when the comet passes over the land for a second time."
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3861
NAME Black Tower, laboratory
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The top floor of the of tower is entirely devoted to a laboratory. Numerous
tables groan under the weight of broken glass and crumbled piles of dust that
used to be parchments of some kind. A large black vat leans precariously
against the west wall, rusting and useless now. Through a black marble arch
in the east wall you can see a catwalk extending through the treetops.
The circular staircase only goes down from here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
